Intruduction

Using R code to import images, create annotations, combine frames to generate a meme, and add animation to transform it into a GIF.

Requirement

R packages:

library(magick)
library(materialmodifier)

R code

#create a new meme
##frame
library(magick)
my_meme <- image_blank(width = 400, height = 400) %>%
  image_annotate("")

##image 1
img_1 = image_read("https://pbs.twimg.com/media/Exa2FEyWUAIGeMD?format=jpg&name=small") %>%
  image_scale(800) %>%
  image_crop("800x489")
homework <- image_blank(width=500,
                        height=488,
                        color="#ffffff") %>%
  image_annotate(text="Let me see \n when the assignment \n is due",
                 color="#000000",
                 size=50,
                 font="sans",
                 gravity="center")

##image 2
img_2 = image_read("https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/a/a4/Hide_the_Pain_Harold_%28Andr%C3%A1s_Arat%C3%B3%29.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(800)
deadline <- image_blank(width=500,
                        height=488,
                        color="#ffffff") %>%
  image_annotate(text="Due date: Yesterday",
                 color="#000000",
                 size=50,
                 font="sans",
                 gravity="center")

##combine
top_row <- image_append(c(img_1, homework))
bottom_row <- image_append(c(img_2, deadline))
final_result <- c(top_row, bottom_row) %>%
  image_append(stack=TRUE) %>%
  image_scale(800)


#save images
image_write(img_1, "images/img_1.png")
image_write(homework, "images/homework.png")
image_write(img_2, "images/img_2.png")
image_write(deadline, "images/deadline.png")

image_write(final_result, "images/my_meme.png")
final_result

#add animation
library(materialmodifier)
##top row
homework_png <- image_read("images/homework.png")
white_frame <- image_blank(width=800, height=489, color="#ffffff")
x_offset <- (800 - image_info(homework_png)$width) / 2
y_offset <- (489 - image_info(homework_png)$height) / 2
frame_1 <- image_composite(white_frame, homework_png, offset = paste0("+", x_offset, "+", y_offset))

frame_2 <- image_read("images/img_1.png")

look_frame <- c(frame_1, frame_2)

##bottom row
ddl_png <- image_read("images/deadline.png")
white_frame <- image_blank(width=800, height=489, color="#ffffff")
x_offset <- (800 - image_info(ddl_png)$width) / 2
y_offset <- (489 - image_info(ddl_png)$height) / 2
frame_5 <- image_composite(white_frame, ddl_png, offset = paste0("+", x_offset, "+", y_offset))

blur_frame_1 <- image_blur(frame_5, 50, 10)
blur_frame_2 <- image_blur(frame_5, 34, 8)
blur_frame_3 <- image_blur(frame_5, 17, 6)
blur_frame_4 <- image_blur(frame_5, 10, 5)
blur_frame_5 <- image_blur(frame_5, 5, 3)

charcoal_frame <- image_charcoal(frame_5)
  
frame_6 <- image_read("images/img_2.png")
image_2 <- im_load("images/img_2.png")
frame_7 <-  image_2 %>%
  modif(effect = c("aging"), strength = c(5)) %>%
  im_save(name = "glow_img2", path = "images")
frame_8 <- image_read("images/glow_img2.png")

effect_frames <- c(blur_frame_1, blur_frame_2, blur_frame_3, blur_frame_4, blur_frame_5, frame_5, charcoal_frame)
effect_times <- c(50, 50, 50, 50, 50, 100, 200)

badend_frame <- c(effect_frames, frame_8)

##combine and save
final_frame <- c(look_frame, badend_frame)
delay_time <- c(250, 100, effect_times, 300)
image_animate(final_frame, fps=1, delay=delay_time) %>%
  image_write("images/my_animation.gif")
